ed. Madden contends that since some of our widely held assumptions about the patterns of Irish history dissolve under scrutiny at the local level, they should be more cautiously applied on a larger scale.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / Europe / Ireland.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357261440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773572614423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773572614/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles